I used 1/2 cup creamy all-natural peanut butter, 4 tbsp lemon juice, 1 tbsp minced garlic, 1/2 tbsp sriacha, 3 tbsp sugar, 3 tbsp fish sauce and 1/2 cup coconut milk...blended till smooth and let sit for about 6 hrs...so yummy and easy too...served it with chicken skewers and shrimp skewers that I baked with a little brush of this sauce on before hand. Rave reviews!

Rating: 3
Good with the modifications that others have said (coconut milk and splash of fish sauce). I found mine very salty- I think it may have been the type of soy sauce I used (gluten free) so I ended up adding 1/6 cup extra peanut butter and 1/6 coconut milk, along with an extra 1/3 cup water).

Rating: 4
I have been so disappointed with store bought peanut sauce, I just have not bothered. I love this Sauce!! I have been craving the peanut sauce at a local Vietnamese restaurant and I devour every drop of it with their Spring rolls. Thanks Kate for having this recipe. I did modify it, with two cloves of garlic, 2 tbs brown sugar, less coconut milk, because I like it a little thicker. Simmer to blend the flavors. Delicious! The fun part, my 8 year old daughter Amira made it and felt like a queen chef! It is so yummy!

